==Korean==
===Noun===
'''해오라기''' (''haeoragi'') 
# white [[heron]], [[egret]]. (This word definitely means a ''white'' bird, whether heron or egret. It is debatable if originally so did ''[[heron]], [[egret]]'', Finnish ''[[haikara]]'', Old High German ''[[heigaro]]'', and its cognates.) 

====Synonyms====
* [[하야로비]] (''hayarobi'') (obsolete), cf. Finnish [[haikara]], Old High German [[heigaro]] 
* [[해오라비]] (''haeorabi'') (obsolete)
* [[해오리]] (''haeori'')
* [[백로]] ([[白鷺]], ''baegro'')
* [[백조]] ([[白鳥]], baegjo, baekjo) 

